annotationA: Heat shock protein 60D, isoform A; ATP binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: response to heat; 'de novo' protein folding; apoptotic process; protein targeting to mitochondrion; protein refolding; Belongs to the chaperonin (HSP60) family
annotationB: Trap1, isoform A; Trap1 is a mitochondrial chaperone protein of the heat shock protein (HSP90) family. It shows an ATPase activity and is involved in neurodegeneration associated with mitochondrial dysfunction
